<HEADLINE> One Killed in Paris House Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 28 (Xinhua) -- A 50-year-old Moroccan man was
killed in a fire which devastated a running down apartment
building in central Paris today, said police.
</P>
<P>
The fire could be caused by an accident in the big building
which was illegally occupied by some 365 North African and black
African people, as the government banned people from inhabiting
the house in July 1997.
</P>
<P>
The mayoral office of Paris said that it had put into place
immediately all the necessary measures to rehouse the people
living in the building, which is situated on Rue Louvel-Tessier in
the 10th district of Paris.
</P>
<P>
Officials said that among the 365 people forced to leave the
building were 15 children, and the government was using a
gymnasium nearby as a temporary shelter for them, before sending
them to emergency houses of the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
