<HEADLINE> Turkish Cypriots Suspend Bi-communal Contacts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, December 28 (Xinhua) -- The Turkish Cypriots have
decided to suspend contacts with the government of Cyprus
controlled by the Greek Cypriots as from Saturday, Turkish Cypriot
press reported today.
</P>
<P>
What will be affected by the decision are bicommual activities
sponsored by foreign countries, especially the United States,
contacts between two communities' trade unionists, business
people, women's organizations, students and professors, the
reports said.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Taner Etkin, "foreign minister" of the
"Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus", a break-away part of
Cyprus, which is recognized only by Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Cypriots are to review the decision of this month by
European Union which is to start accession negotiations with
Cyprus next March, but exclude Turkey, Etkin said.
</P>
<P>
European Union's decision has angered the Turkish Cypriots,
whose leader Rauf Denktash has claimed the negotiations between
the two communities are "dead," and that he will no longer discuss
the subject with the U.N. and the Cypriot government.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister of Cyprus Ioannis Kasoulides criticized the
decision of the Turkish Cypriots on Saturday, calling it an
"extortionist move."
</P>
<P>
He said that the negative policy of the Turkish Cypriots toward
the EU will prove damaging for them.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus was divided into a Greek Cypriot-controlled south and
Turkish Cypriot-controlled north in 1974 when Turkey landed its
troops and took over the northern third of the island after an
abortive pro-Athens coup by the Greek Cypriots.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. and some countries, including the U.S., have been
making efforts to help reunify Cyprus based on a bi-zonal and
bi-communal formula. But so far little tangible results have been
achieved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
