<HEADLINE> French Extreme-Right Urges Resignation of Prefect </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 28 (Xinhua) -- France's extreme-right National
Front (FN) today urged the resignation of the prefect of the
French overseas island territory of Martinique, after its leader
Jean-Marie Le Pen was rounded up by protesters at the airport of
the Caribbean island Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"No matter it is simply because of his incompetence or because
of his negligence which openly covered an operation of the
hooligans, the responsibility of the prefect is heavily involved.
He should go," said the party's national secretary in charge of
overseas territories and departments, Huguette Fatna, in a
published statement.
</P>
<P>
Le Pen was rounded up by some 50 militants of the independence
movement of Martinique Thursday at the airport of
Fort-de-France/Lamentin before he flew to Porto Rico.
</P>
<P>
The protesters attacked Le Pen for his remarks on "racial
inequality" and on the gas chambers of Nazi death camps, which he
said were "a point of detail in the history of World War II."
</P>
</TEXT>
