<HEADLINE> 21 Villagers Killed in Newest Violence in Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 28 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-one villagers were killed
from Friday night till Saturday morning in a village near Medea,
80 kilometers south of the Algerian capital Algiers, said reports
from Algeria today.
</P>
<P>
The victims were 11 men, three women and seven children aged
from two to nine, who belonged to three families, said the reports.
</P>
<P>
From 145 to 184 people have been killed since last Tuesday in
Algeria, according to reports. Most of the killings took place in
the region of Tiaret 200 kilometers southwest of Algiers.
</P>
<P>
Seven children aged from seven to 14 were abducted Saturday
when they were guarding cattle on the Chenoua mountain west of
Algiers, said the reports.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, seven Islamic militants were reportedly killed by
security forces in Algiers, Boumerdes 50 kilometers east of
Algiers and Medea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
