<HEADLINE> Iraq Accuses US of Interference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, December 28 (Xinhua) -- Iraq today said the recent
U.S. talks with Turkey on protecting Kurds in northern Iraq
revealed the two are conspiring to carry out a U.S.-British scheme
of interfering in Iraq's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
The official Iraqi News Agency quoted an unidentified spokesman
as saying the U.S. has been, and is still working to spread
disorder and instability in northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
He spokesman accused Washington of making northern Iraq an
arena for bloody internal conflicts and a target of Turkish
military attacks and invasion as well as foreign intelligence
violations.
</P>
<P>
He was responding to a Voice of America report Saturday that
U.S. President Bill Clinton discussed with Turkish Prime Minister
Mesut Yilmaz efforts to continue pressuring Iraq with the view of
protecting Iraqi Kurds.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that by agitating Ankara in the wrong way,
the U.S. has inflicted heavy security and economic damage upon
Turkey, damage that can not be made up by U.S. promises to support
Turkey's request to join the European Union and cooperation in the
field of energy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
