<HEADLINE> French Communist Party Urges Emergency Housing of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 28 (Xinhua) -- The Communist deputies of the
Paris Municipal Council today called for the immediate requisition
of a house to shelter the 365 people forced out of a running down
house by fire in central Paris.
</P>
<P>
The fire resulted in the death of one Moroccan man and the
homelessness of the rest of people squatting in the house,
including 150 children and most of them North Africans and black
Africans.
</P>
<P>
The deputies from the Communist Party of France (PCF) said in a
communique that they had been alarming for years the situation in
the house situated on Rue Louvel-Tessier in the 10th district of
Paris.
</P>
<P>
"The city council of Paris cannot wait for the spring to assume
its responsibilities. It should put into work everything so that a
house be immediately requisitioned in the 10th district to let all
these families to shelter themselves there," said the deputies.
</P>
</TEXT>
