<HEADLINE> French Union Urges Emergency Measures After </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 28 (Xinhua) -- The French trade unin Force
Ouvriere (FO) today called for emergency measures against violent
acts against public transport after a public streetcar was stoned
Saturday night by troublemakers in Mulhouse, eastern France.
</P>
<P>
The FO secretary in charge of transport, Roger Poletti,
expressed his "entire support" to the streetcar workers of
Mulhouse after this attack.
</P>
<P>
But he regretted that the workers once stopped providing
service to the district considered to be "hot," after the accident
took place.
</P>
<P>
"The refusal to serve the most disadvantaged districts divides
the nation into different speed tracks. This cannot but be
provisionary because it jeopardizes the essential nature of public
service itself," he said.
</P>
<P>
Several attacks against public transport drivers or vehicles
took place during this Christmas season, causing traffic confusion
in some cities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
