<HEADLINE> Russian First Deputy PM Leaves for China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 28 (Xinhua) -- Russian First Deputy Prime
Minister Boris Nemtsov left here for China today to sign a major
atomic contract.
</P>
<P>
The intergovernmental general contract on the construction of a
Lianyungang nuclear power plant in Jiangsu province, China, was
considered during the visit by Russian President Boris Yeltsin to
China in November.
</P>
<P>
According to Nemtsov, the contract will be the biggest for
Russia in 1997, the cost of which exceeds 3 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
