<HEADLINE> UNIP Says It Wants Genuine Dialog </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 28 (Xinhua) -- The United National
Independence Party (UNIP) led by former Zambian president Kenneth
Kaunda said here today that it wants genuine and serious dialog
to resolve the issues which are at the center of the political
impasse in the country.
</P>
<P>
UNIP National Chairman Malimba Masheke told a news briefing at
UNIP headquarters that "Zambia is a big country. We can't all be
friends but we can all be patriots prepared to talk to all
leaders in their various political parties whether we like them
or not."
</P>
<P>
The dialog to be held at the end of this month is "nothing but
a futile exercise in trickery, which will achieve nothing," he
said.
</P>
<P>
He predicted that there will be no agreement on amending the
contentious clauses in the constitution and there will be no
agreement on a new and commonly accepted register of voters.
</P>
<P>
There will be no agreement on setting up a truly independent
electoral commission, he said.
</P>
<P>
No one should be cheated that the ruling Movement for
Multi-Party Democracy (MMD) want real dialog and all they want is
a window dressing exercise so that they can get donor funding for
their budget, Masheke said.
</P>
<P>
He demanded Kaunda's immediate release without conditions.
</P>
<P>
Micheal Sata, co-chairman of the inter-party talks and
government minister without portfolio said here today that the
proposed inter-party dialog will go ahead as scheduled on
December 30 and 31.
</P>
<P>
After Kaunda was arrested by police on Thursday a number of
parties announced their withdrawal from the inter-party dialogs
including UNIP.
</P>
<P>
At the preliminary meeting held early this month 31 parties
drew an agenda for the inter-party dialog. The agenda includes
most contentious issues like constitution, electoral process and
voters' register and fresh registration.
</P>
<P>
Before Kaunda's arrest 28 parties confirmed their
participation of the dialog, which was originally scheduled early
next month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
