<HEADLINE> Mongolian Party Issues New Year Message </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The Mongolian People's
Revolutionary Party reviewed its achievements today in a new year
message to its members and the whole nation.
</P>
<P>
In the message from the party's Leadership Council, it said,
in the past year, the party successfully held its 22nd Congress,
conducted major reforms on fundamental policies and activities,
and established theoretical principles based on democratic
socialism for the nation.
</P>
<P>
It added that with reform in 1997 the party won great
victories in both the presidential election and the supplementary
election of The Great Hural.
</P>
<P>
These victories, it noted, demonstrated that the party enjoyed
support from its members and the people, and was the most
influential political force in Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Party Chairman Nambaryn Enhbayar revealed in a press
conference that in 1997, about 7,000 people joined the party, of
them, 85 percent were under 35 years of age.
</P>
<P>
The party now has a membership of 86,000, the biggest
among all Mongolian political parties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
