<DOCNO> XIE19971229.0030 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton to Order Effort to Sign Up Medicaid Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 29 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
will soon order a major effort to sign up millions of children who
are eligible for Medicaid but not enrolled in the program, The New
York Times reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted unidentified White House officials as
saying that Clinton was dismayed to find that most states had made
little progress in enrolling children from low-income families
last year.
</P>
<P>
Medicaid, the federal health insurance program paid by
federal-state matching funds, covers more than 30 million poor,
elderly and disabled Americans.
</P>
<P>
Officials said Clinton will order Federal and state agencies
late next month to step up their efforts by dispatching Medicaid
eligibility workers to hospital, clinics, day care center, schools
and factories.
</P>
<P>
Federal health officials said that at least three million
children were eligible for Medicaid bu not enrolled, nearly
one-third of the nation's 10 million uninsured children, the
newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
More than 18 million children are now served by Medicaid in the
United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
