<HEADLINE> NPC Standing Committee Meeting Concludes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The 29th Meeting of the
Standing Committee of the Eighth National People's Congress (NPC),
China's top legislature, concluded today following the passage of
three laws and an important resolution.
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi, chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, presided over
today's meeting.
</P>
<P>
The three laws passed were on blood donations, prices and
earthquake safety, all of which go into effect next year.
</P>
<P>
At today's meeting the NPC Standing Committee also adopted a
resolution that sets an agenda for the First Session of the Ninth
National People's Congress, which is expected to convene on March
5.
</P>
<P>
According to the resolution, the March meeting will hear and
examine the government report, and elect new top government
leaders.
</P>
<P>
A number of reports on reviewing results of bills of the
presidium of the NPC Fifth Session presented by the Nationalities
Committee, Law Committee, Foreign Affairs Committee and Committee
for Internal and Judicial Affairs were also passed at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Several decisions on removals and appointments also passed at
the meeting.  
</P>
