<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1997: Epoch-making Events to Decide China's Future (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Misgivings that the fate of the country solely rested upon
Deng are fading along with 1997. People are beginning to
understand why Deng had devoted so much attention to political
restructuring, especially in maintaining a smooth transition of power
and lasting political stability during his remaining years.
</P>
<P>
What is more important is that the Deng Xiaoping Theory, which
guides the reforms and opening-up of China, has been endowed with
more authority.
</P>
<P>
Ever since Jiang Zemin, general secretary of the CPC Central
Committee, twice called on the party to hold high the great banner
of the theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics
put forward by Deng Xiaoping, both in his memorial speech at
Deng's funeral in February and his speech in the Party School of
the CPC Central Committee in May. In September, Deng Xiaoping
Theory was formally written into the Party Constitution in the
15th CPC National Congress. Many believe this will have a
far-reaching impact on the country's future.
</P>
<P>
Through the year 1997, it has never been more likely that the
promise -- "never waver for a hundred years in adhering to the
Party's basic line" -- will endure. The country's basic policy of
making economic construction the central task, and taking the path
of reforms and opening-up, will not waver from any interference --
either from the left or the right -- nor from any change in the
composition of Chinese leadership.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971229.0038 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1997: Epoch-making Events to Decide China's Future (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It is reasonable to assume that Hong Kong will achieve
long-term prosperity and stability and China will finally achieve
the peaceful reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, China's frequent and fruitful foreign relations
during the year have captured the attention of the world as well.
Headed by President Jiang Zemin's official visit to the United
States and a couple of Sino-Russian Summit Talks within the year,
China's diplomatic relations have entered a new era by forming
harmonious relationships with both neighboring countries and more
distant ones such as South Africa. There is no doubt that China
will play a more important role in regional and international
affairs.
</P>
<P>
Marked by the successful accomplishment of its "soft-landing,"
China has bid farewell to a shortage of goods. By now, the
country has entered a new era which focuses on better economic
structure and the improvement of general economic strength.
</P>
<P>
With endeavors in the past four years, China has successfully
landed on the track of "high economic growth rate and low
inflation," thus achieving a stable economy in the initial stages
of economic take-off.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971229.0039 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1997: Epoch-making Events to Decide China's Future (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Despite these unprecedented achievements, Chinese leaders have
remained calm. The country has been lauded for its effective
macro-economic control efforts, which have allowed China to rise
above the ominous Southeast Asian financial crisis. It also has
improved its financial system and made strides to reduce redundant
constructions.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the country is bravely carrying out the reforms of
state-owned enterprises and the re-employment programs for a dozen
million laid-off workers. Such strenuousness is unrivaled
worldwide.
</P>
<P>
With its focus on economic development, China has expressed its
cordial wish for peace. In the 15th National Party Congress, Jiang
Zemin, general secretary of the CPC Central Committee, declared
that 500,000 servicemen will be demobilized within three
years. The country also articulated its willingness to be a "good
neighbor, good partner, good friend" with member countries of the
Association of Southeast Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
Among all political slogans in China in 1997, Jiang's remark of
"the banner is the direction, the banner is the image" will
undoubtedly be the most popular.
</P>
<P>
While the press is crowning the year 1997 with such adjectives
as "extraordinary" and "epoch-making", the average Chinese has a
deeper understanding: Doesn't the image China presents with its
adherence to the Deng Xiaoping Theory rightly reveal the direction
the country will follow in the future? 
</P>
</TEXT>
