<HEADLINE> Iraq's KDP Leader Condemns Turkish Incursion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Secretary-general of the
Kurdish Democratic Party (KDP) of Iraq Ahmed Mohammed Saeed
al-Atrooshy today condemned Turkey's new military incursion into
northern Iraq, demanding immediate withdrawal of Turkish troops.
</P>
<P>
In a statement to Iraqi News Agency (INA), al-Atrooshy said
Turkey's continued violation of Iraq's sovereignty under false
pretexts proves the hostility of Turkey, which run counter to
international law and norms as well as principles of good
neighborliness.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has said the objective of its cross-border operations
is to wipe out the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK)
militants who seek shelter in northern Iraq and launch attacks on
Turkish targets from there.
</P>
<P>
PKK has been fighting against the Turkish government since 1984
to establish an independent state in eastern and southeastern
Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Turkish troops launched the latest cross-border attack on PKK
militants two days ago.
</P>
<P>
Al-Atrooshy said that Turkey has taken advantage of the
abnormal situation in northern Iraq and has caused great harm to
inhabitants in the region. 
</P>
