<HEADLINE> UNDP Approves Grant for Dhaka Environment Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Development
Program (UNDP) Approved on Monday a grant of 26 million U.S.
dollars for an environment program in Bangladesh, the national
news agency BSS reported.
</P>
<P>
Under an agreement signed here on Monday between Bangladesh and
UNDP, the sustainable environment program was aimed at helping
implement the country's national environment management action
plan (NEMAP) which was steered by the Ministry of Environment and
Forest.
</P>
<P>
The 26 million dollar program, the first major program to
implement NEMAP, focuses on five major areas: policy and
institutions, participatory ecosystem management, community based
on environmental sanitation, awareness and advocacy, and training
and education.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-one official institutions will co-implement the new
program with the government.  
</P>
