<HEADLINE> China Sentences two to death for robbing cultural relics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Two convicted criminals were
sentenced to death for stealing stone sculptures from Tang Dynasty
(618-907) tombs in northwest China's Shaanxi province, China's
Supreme People's Court announced here today.
</P>
<P>
On May 3 Han Huamin and Sun Guobin smashed five stone figurines
in front of a Tang Dynasty Emperor's tomb and then took the heads
to Guangzhou. One of the five stone heads was lost during
transportation; the other four were sold for 40,000 yuan (5,000
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
According to the Shaanxi Cultural Relics Appraisal Committee,
the stone figurines were under the top state protection.
</P>
<P>
The local intermediate people's court gave the two robbers a
death sentence after the first trial. The men lodged an appeal
which was rejected by the Shaanxi Higher People's Court.
</P>
<P>
The death sentence was executed today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
