investments between Zambia and Zimbabwe for the benefit of the
two countries and expressed his concern at the "continued
harrassment" of "innocent " travellers by the Zimbabwean
immigration officials at the border.
</P>
<P>
Zambia has always complained that it suffers unfavourable
trade imbalance with its neignbours. The Zambian government even
termed the country as a "dumping ground" in the sub-region and
called on its neighbours, Zimbabwe and South Africa in
particular, to eliminate their trade barriers.
</P>
<P>
During a cocktail party in Lusaka Sunday, Zimbabwean Foreign
Minister Stanislus Mudenge who came to attend the 11th commission
meeting said that the warm political relations existing between
the two neighbours have created a "conducive" economic
environment and broadened bilateral trade opportunities.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the strong bond of friendship that the two
countries enjoy has laid a good foundation for enhanced trade
between them.
</P>
<P>
Mudenge stressed the need to eliminate all trade barriers so
as to stimulater trade between Zambia and Zimbabwe. 
</P>
