<HEADLINE> Top Legislature Decides on New NPC's Agenda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 29 (Xinhua)-- China has decided to convene
the first session of the Ninth National People's Congress on March
5 in Beijing. The new legislature will elect top state and
government leaders.
</P>
<P>
The 29th meeting of the NPC Standing Committee passed a
resolution before it closed here this afternoon which sets forth
suggestions for the session's agenda.
</P>
<P>
According to the resolution, the new legislature's first
session will hear and examine the government report, examine and
approve the national economic and social development plan for 1998
and the state budget for 1998.
</P>
<P>
Also, it will hear three work reports by the NPC Standing
Committee, the Supreme People's Court and the Supreme People's
Procuratorate.
</P>
<P>
The new legislature will elect the chairman and vice chairmen
for its Standing Committee, elect the country's president and vice
presidents. It will decide on the list of the State Council's
premier and vice premiers, as well as state councillors and
ministers for all government departments and heads of the Supreme
People's Court and Supreme People's Procuratorate.
</P>
<P>
According to the Chinese Constitution, the National People's
Congress serves a term of five years. 
</P>
