<HEADLINE> HK Emigrant Number Sets Decade Low This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The number of Hong Kong
people emigrated this year is estimated to reach 30,900, setting a
record low over the decade.
</P>
<P>
This represented a 20 percent drop compared with 40,300
emigrants last year, local press reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
There are signs that emigrants are expected to decrease further
next year due to the stable political and economic situation in
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the number of foreigners residing in Hong Kong has
been on the gradual rise.
</P>
<P>
Over the past seven years, its annual average increase has
surpassed over 10 percent, thus bringing the total number of
foreigners residing in Hong Kong to 500,000 including those
emigrants who have returned to Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The largest number is the Philippines totaling 150,000,
followed by the United States, Indonesia, Canada and
Britain. 
</P>
