<HEADLINE> Iraq, Jordan Sign Agreement on Oil Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Iraq and Jordan signed an
agreement on oil cooperation here today, under which Iraq will
supply Jordan with 4.8 million tons of oil next year at a
referential price, according to Iraqi News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by Iraqi Oil Minister Amir Mohammed
Rashid and visiting Jordanian Minister of Energy and Mineral
Resources Mohammed Saleh Hourani.
</P>
<P>
