<HEADLINE> 90th Anniversary of Chinese Modern Drama Marked in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 29 (Xinhua) -- A major celebration marking
the 90th anniversary of the birth of the Chinese modern drama was
held at the Great Hall of People here this morning.
</P>
<P>
Li Lanqing, member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party (CPC) Central Committee and
Vice Premier attended the celebration, expressing greetings to the
dramatists and performers who have made great contribution to the
development of modern drama in China.
</P>
<P>
Li Tieying, member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central
Committee, made a speech at the celebration, urging cultural
departments and drama troupes to develop more dramas with the
theme of reflecting people's true life in modern China.
</P>
<P>
Some 600 dramatists and artists attended the event, and 720
senior artists nationwide who have devoted themselves to the
Chinese modern drama for 50 years or more were awarded by the
Ministry of Culture, sponsor of the celebration.
</P>
<P>
Chinese modern drama started with Wang Zhongsheng in 1907 when
his drama troupe Chun Yan (Spring Sun) put on stage "Uncle Tom's
Cabin" in Shanghai as the first Chinese drama. 
</P>
