<DOCNO> XIE19971229.0085 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Achieving Progress in Market Economy Drive (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 29 (Xinhua) --China has made marked progress
in its drive of building socialist market economy, with the new
system taking a dominant position in China's economic life.
</P>
<P>
So far, 90 percent of the country's gross domestic product
(GDP) have been achieved through market circulation, Lu Yonghua,
director of the Research Office of the State Commission for
Economic Restructuring, made the remarks in an interview with
Xinhua today.
</P>
<P>
According to official, over 85 percent of capital goods, more
than 90 percent of industrial finished products and over 95
percent of means of subsistence now depend on market for price
adjustments, and capital goods and means of subsistence under
state mandatory plan have dropped from 1,000 kinds or so five
years ago to the present 30 kinds.
</P>
<P>
Lu said the progress is also felt in an all-round development
of market mechanism, establishment of a macro control system,
formation of an economic pattern featuring simultaneous growth of
diversified economic factors with public ownership as the
dominant force, and formation of a all-round opening-up pattern,
in addition to greater role of the market in adjusting
distribution of resources and economic life.
</P>
<P>
The drive of establishing a socialist market economy was
decided in 1992 at the 14th National Congress of the Communist
Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
Under the goal, China hopes to build up the framework of
socialist market economy by the turn of this century and develop
such system early next century.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971229.0086 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Achieving Progress in Market Economy Drive (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Through adjusting ownership structure and developing
economy of non-public ownership and of mixed ownerships, China's
state-owned economic force now contributes 28.8 percent of the
country's industrial output value, and collective economic force
contributes 44.4 percent, while economic force of non-public
ownership contributes 30.8 percent instead of 13.4 percent in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, circulation of three quarters or so of the commodities
are now undertaken by economic force of non-public ownership.
</P>
<P>
Markets of capital, technologies, property rights, futures and
labor have been developing rapidly in China. In 1997 alone, more
than 800 listed companies pooled 150 billion yuan of funds through
stock markets.
</P>
<P>
China has also planned to set up specialized markets of
entrepreneurs and managers beginning from next year, with the
purpose of offering more professional management personnel of
higher level for state-owned enterprises to carry out reforms.
</P>
<P>
Out of the present 2,000 billion yuan of total social
investment annually in the country, state investment only accounts
for five percent or so, various production and business
institutions have become leading forces of investment.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the Ministry of Internal Trade said retail
prices of state-controlled social commodities have fallen from 20
percent to 7.2 percent thanks to the formation of the
market pricing mechanism.
</P>
<P>
An overwhelming majority of the country's 300,000 state-owned
enterprises have learned to arrange production according the
market demands, and only 10,000 of the state-owned enterprises are
designated to fulfill state-set plans.
</P>
<P>
One-third plus of China's 14,000 state-owned large and
medium-sized enterprises have established standardized corporate
systems. And 50 to 70 percent of the state-owned small
enterprises have completed system transformation or organizational
reshuffle.
</P>
<P>
Well-known Chinese economist Ma Hong say that China has formed
a buyers' market and its relationship with the international
market has becoming closer and closer, and the degree of China's
economic development depending on overseas market will be up from
10 percent to 40 percent.
</P>
<P>
"With the accelerated establishment of China's market economy
and globalization of the world economy, China can keep improving
its economic structure and efficiency only by developing an
economy on market demands," said the economist.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
