<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Air Macao started on Monday a
chartered air service between Macao and Nanjing, capital of east
China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
There will be two round flights each week on Monday and Friday
respectively, with the air traveling time of two hours and ten
minutes, a spokesman for the air company said.
</P>
<P>
Nanjing has become Air Macao's seventh destination in China's
inland, following Beijing, Shanghai, Fuzhou, Xiamen, Wuhan and
Qingdao. It is also the 11th destination of the air company.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Yunda, deputy general manager of Air Macao, said that the
new air route targets passengers from Taiwan, like previous
service to Beijing, Shanghai, Fuzhou and Xiamen. Passengers will
be able to enjoy quasi-direct flight service between Taiwan and
Nanjing.
</P>
<P>
Zhou said his company plans to start regular flight service to
Chongqing city in southeast China early next year.
</P>
<P>
Air Macao now has a fleet of six planes, including four Airbus
A-321s and two Airbus A320s.  
