<HEADLINE> Dusk to Dawn Curfew Imposed Along Indo-Pak Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 29 (Xinhua)-- A dusk to dawn curfew was
imposed along the Indo-Pakistan five km border for two months from
Sunday by India-held Jammu District Magistrate Suresh Kumar, Press
Trust of India (PTI) said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The curfew will remain in force from 06:00 PM to 0600 AM (local
time). In exceptional circumstances, the station house officer or
post commander of the nearest border security force may permit any
person or persons to move about during the curfew period, PTI
quoted an order, which was issued Sunday, as saying.
</P>
<P>
The step has been taken to prevent smuggling of weapons and
subversive elements from across the border, the order said.
