<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Production of Philippines' Manufacturing Sector Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The production value and volume
of the Philippines' manufacturing sector registered annual
increases of 8.1 percent and 4.3 percent respectively in October
despite the on-going economic crisis in the country, the National
Statistics Office said Monday.
</P>
<P>
"The value of production index (VPI) in key manufacturing
enterprises rose by 8.1 percent to 484.9 in October 1997 from
448.7 last year," the office said in a report released here.
</P>
<P>
It said that on a month-on-month comparison, the VPI increased
by 0.4 from 483.0 in September.
</P>
<P>
These figures were based on the results of the Survey of Key
Enterprises in Manufacturing, a regular monthly survey by the
office aimed to provide flash indictors on the performance of key
manufacturing enterprises in the country.
</P>
<P>
The office said that the year-on-year increases were observed
in 11 out of the 16 major sectors.
</P>
<P>
Electrical machinery, with an 82.2 percent growth, contributed
the biggest share of 69.6 percent to the year-on-year growth of
VPI due to the gains in production of micro-circuits, the office
said.
</P>
<P>
It was followed by chemicals, a 14.2 percent increase, and
petroleum products, a 6.6 percent increase, with a 10.3 percent
contribution each to the year-on-year growth, it said.
</P>
<P>
"The volume of production index (VOPI) for key manufacturing
enterprises was estimated at 158.8 in October 1997, registering a
year-on-year growth of 4.3 percent," the office said.
</P>
<P>
The office said that electrical machinery, with the biggest
increase of 86.9 percent, contributed a share of 91 percent to the
year-on-year growth, while beverage and non-metallic mineral
products followed with increases of 25.7 percent and 4.4 percent,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
However, petroleum refineries decreased by 11.2 percent,
wearing apparel by 34.5 percent, paper and paper products by 40.6
percent and transport equipment by 26.7 percent in the month, it
said.
</P>
<P>
On a monthly basis, the VOPI increased by 0.2 percent from
158.6 in September, the office said.
</P>
<P>
The October performance of the sector indicates that the
negative effects of the financial crisis in the country had not
been felt heavily by the manufacturing enterprises yet in the
month.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
