<HEADLINE> Small Thermal Power Plants in China to Be Closed Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The State Power Corporation
will close down small thermal power plants with a total installed
capacity of 10.86 million kilowatts in the next three years,
according to an ongoing national power conference here.
</P>
<P>
The "People's Daily" quoted a leading official of the Power
Ministry as saying that the move is aimed at optimizing the power
structure.
</P>
<P>
"The progress of closing down small thermal power plants will
be connected with the approval of construction of large power
plants in the locality," the official said.
</P>
<P>
He asked the provinces of Guangdong, Henan, Jiangsu and
Zhejiang, which are blamed for slack management of the small
thermal power plants, to take a lead in the drive next year.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that the building of power grids should be a
priority for the development of the power industry.
</P>
<P>
Shandong Province in east China recently took the first move to
shut down a smoothly-operating small thermal power plant for the
sake of environmental protection. The province has 193 such small
thermal power plants which consume large amounts of energy and
pollute the environment seriously.
</P>
<P>
China's per-capita power consumption amounts to only one third
of the world's average. Currently, the country has 11 counties
without power supply and 60 million people have no access to
power.  
</P>
</TEXT>
