<HEADLINE> Scientists Develop Cobalt-60 Container Check-Up System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists have
developed a Cobalt-60 container check-up system which can find as
small as a cake of soap in a container full of goods in three
minutes.
</P>
<P>
Experts here said it is the first container check-up system of
the kind in the world and its price only accounts for 20 percent
of the foreign accelerator-rayed check-up systems.
</P>
<P>
The fast-speed check-up system has been developed by
scientists at the Nuclear technology Design Institute of Qinghua
University after 15 months efforts.
</P>
<P>
The system has recently passed the appraisal by a group of
academicians of Chinese Academy of Engineering and experts from
other research institutions.
</P>
<P>
The safety of biological products and foods can be guaranteed
as the goods only receive 1 percent as much radiation dosage as
that of making an X-ray check up of a man.
</P>
<P>
They believed that the newly developed system will be effective
device for the nation's anti-smuggle work.
</P>
<P>
So far, some 150 customs houses in China need to install such a
system.  
</P>
</TEXT>
