<HEADLINE> China's 1st DSS in Shipping Management Passes Assessment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 29 (Xinhua) -- China's first Decision-Support
System (DSS) for management in shipping industry passed assessment
in north China's port city of Tianjin City on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The software system has been jointly developed by the Tianjin
Branch of the China Ocean Shipping Group (COSCO Tianjin) and the
Dalian Maritime University.
</P>
<P>
Experts from Tianjin University and COSCO agreed that the
system will have a profound impact on China's shipping industry.
</P>
<P>
The system is advanced, practical and reliable, and creative as
well, they concluded.
</P>
<P>
They proposed commercializing the system so as to spread its use
in the whole shipping industry. The system will be put to use in
COSCO Tianjin on January 1, 1998.
</P>
<P>
According to Wei Jiafu, general manager of COSCO Tianjin and
chief of the joint DSS-developing group, the system has three main
systems, namely the general manager DSS, the vessel-operation DSS,
and the investment DSS, and nine sub-systems.
</P>
<P>
The 47 year-old general manager told Xinhua that as China is
shifting from a planned economy to a market economy, shipping
companies have to practice a modern and scientific management
system, in a bid to compete on the world market.
</P>
<P>
Wei, a former captain and leader of many other major shipping
companies in the country, started to develop the system soon after
he came to COSCO Tianjin two years ago.
</P>
<P>
COSCO Tianjin was set up in October 1, 1970. Since then, the
number of its ocean-going fleet has grown from 10 vessels of
137,000 DWT to more than 100 vessels of two million DWT. 
</P>
</TEXT>
