<HEADLINE> Cholera Kills 142 Ugandans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 29 (Xinhua) --Cholera has killed 142
Ugandans so far among a total of 1,523 cases registered in the
country, "The New Vision" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The cholera outbreak started early this month during this rain
season. The most hit areas are the capital and central Mpigi
District, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The epidemic has spread to central Luwero District where it
claimed 30 lives within two weeks before December 18 and
affected 99 people.
</P>
<P>
Some people have been infected with the disease in western
district of Kasese, but there is no death report from there so far,
said a report reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Mulago Hospital, the main health institution of the country,
has received 160 cholera patients during Christmas days, said
Fredrick Ssenkima, the principal health educator in Health
Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Among the patients, 154 are from the city of Kampala, and the
other six are from central Luwero District, he added.
</P>
<P>
The outbreak of cholera is caused by lack of clean drinking
water in rain season. The flood damaged drainage in cities and
towns and the water sources were contaminated, according to the
report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
