<HEADLINE> Real Estate Market in Tianjin Thriving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The real estate market has
been developing vigorously in Tianjin, the largest port city in
north China, since 1994.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the municipal government has taken
a wide range of reform steps to enliven the real estate market
over the past four years.
</P>
<P>
The reform measures include selling government-built apartments
to employees, leasing the right to use land for housing
construction, encouraging different enterprises and institutions
to raise funds for housing construction, and establishing public
housing funds.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, some 23 billion yuan have been pooled
for construction of housing in the city. And the municipality has
leased the land-use right for 1,296 plots, with a total area of
31.39 sq km, for housing construction.
</P>
<P>
New apartments with a combined floor space of 20.6 million sq m
have been constructed with the raised funds and put onto the
market, said the local sources.
</P>
<P>
A total of 500,000 residents have improved their housing
conditions by purchasing new apartments from the market. The per
capita floor space of urban dwellers has now increased to 7.7 sq m
from 6.9 sq m.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin now has 1,142 real estate developers, up from only
eight in 1994. In the first nine months this year, 4.49 billion
yuan was spent constructing new apartments, a rise of 20 percent
from the same period last year. During the same period,
open-market apartments with a total floor space of 1.12 million sq
m were sold. 
</P>
</TEXT>
