<HEADLINE> China's NPC Standing Committee Holds Plenary Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The 29th Session of the
Standing Committee of the Eighth National People's Congress held a
full meeting here this morning.
</P>
<P>
NPC Standing Committee Chairman Qiao Shi attended the plenum,
which was presided over by vice-chairman of the Standing
Committee Lei Jieqiong.
</P>
<P>
The meeting heard a report by director of the NPC Law Committee
Xue Ju on the revision of the drafts of the price law, the law on
blood donation and the law on earthquake prevention.
</P>
<P>
The three laws' revised drafts were examined by the legislature
between December 24 and 25.
</P>
<P>
Xue said that the members of the NPC Standing Committee agreed
that the drafts are pretty good now after they were repeatedly
revised in light of the opinions and suggestions made by the
Standing Committee members and some departments and experts
concerned.
</P>
<P>
"They suggested the legislature approve the three laws at its
current session," Xue said.
</P>
<P>
This morning's plenary meeting also held a forum at which Sun
Tingfang, a member of the Standing Committee, made a speech on the
quality of medicines made from animal organs.
</P>
<P>
Nie Dajiang and Xu Jing, also members of the Standing
Committee, spoke about the urgency of saving and protecting the
historical documents and papers stored in Tibet's local
museums. They made a trip to Tibet early this year.
</P>
<P>
Standing Committee member Huang Yicheng appealed to the Beijing
municipal government to take effective measures to reduce air
pollution in the city.
</P>
<P>
Other members spoke on the issues of investments in higher
education, reemployment of laid-off workers, and rural
finance.  
</P>
