<HEADLINE> Russian Climber Feared Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Russian climber Anatoly
Bukreyev was probably dead after he encountered an avalanche
during his ascent of 8,091-meter Mount Annapurna, Nepal's Tourism
Ministry said on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said 39-year-old Bukreyev was scaling the mountain
with Italian climber Simone Moro when the avalanche struck them at
5,900 meters on December 25.
</P>
<P>
Bukreyev was lost on the mountain and feared dead, but Moro
survived.
</P>
<P>
M. Iriro and L. Rashnar conquered Mount Annapurna on June 3,
1950 to become the first men who successively scaled a mountain
which is above 8,000 meters. 
</P>
