<DOCNO> XIE19971229.0152 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Completes 50 Major Pollution Control Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Beijing has completed 50 major
dust, noise and water pollution control projects this year.
</P>
<P>
"The projects have solved a number of pollution problems
cared by the public and improved the environmental quality in
some regions," said an official with the municipal government.
</P>
<P>
An asphalt concrete plant in the city's Chaoyang District has
been moved for its serious noise and dust pollution, reported today's
Beijing Daily.
</P>
<P>
At a cost of 140 million yuan (about 17.5 million US dollars),
the plant has set up a new factory equipped with pollution control
facilities in Changping County of Beijing, greatly reducing its
dust emission.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the city has enabled all its suburban gas stations
to supply lead-free gas.
</P>
<P>
The city has planned to build 40 "coal-free districts" in its
urban areas by the end of the century to further protect the
environment.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
