<HEADLINE> Indian BJP Party Favors to Review Efficacy of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The Bharatiya Janata Party's
(BJP) Prime Ministerial candidate Atal Behari Vajpayee is in favor
of setting up a Constitution Commission to review the efficacy of
the Indian Constitution in grappling with the problems of the
nation over the past 45 years.
</P>
<P>
"The Commission comprising experts in constitutional law,
education, social service, economics, history, science and
technology and other facets of national life may suggest changes,
additions and alterations to suit the changing needs of the
present and the challenges of the future," Vajpayee said in an
exclusive interview with The Hindustan Times Sunday, which was
made public here Monday.
</P>
<P>
A review of the Constitution was imperative in the light of the
prevailing political instability both at the Center and in some
states, frequent elections and the misuse of the constitutional
provisions for narrow political and personal gains, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The younger generation that is to man the nation in the
immediate future is losing faith in the system," he further said.
</P>
<P>
The BJP, one of the two major national parties in India, has
already expressed its desire to form next government after the
United Front government tendered its resignation on December 4.
</P>
</TEXT>
