<HEADLINE> Death Toll Rises to 10 in Brazilian Prison Riots </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, December 28 (Xinhua) -- A prisoner and a hostage were
killed in an ongoing Brazilian prison unrest on Sunday, which
raised the death toll in recent prison riots in the country to 10.
</P>
<P>
Police said that about 300 visitors and 17 prison guards were held
hostage when the riot occurred at the Sorocaba prison near Sao
Paulo in southeast Brazil.
</P>
<P>
One inmate and a visitor who had been taken hostage were killed
during the rebellion and the situation remained unchanged Sunday
evening, said a prison spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Police believe that the two pistols and five revolvers used by
the rebel prisoners had been smuggled into the prison by outsiders
during visiting hours.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Sunday, police crushed another uprising in the prison
near the Sorocaba facility.
</P>
<P>
Although 192 prisoners rebelled in that case, nobody was killed or
injured as the rebels agreed to return to their cells peacefully in
the end.
</P>
<P>
However, the prison riot that took place in the northeastern
town of Fortaleza on Thursday left eight inmates dead.
</P>
<P>
Brazil has been hit by a spate of prison rebellions in recent
months as prisoners complained about overcrowded cells and demanded
an improvement on living conditions. 
</P>
