<HEADLINE> Beijing Has 600,000 Mobile Phone Subscribers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital has
seen continuous growth in the number of mobile phone subscribers,
with more than 300,000 added this year alone, which exceeds the
total in the previous 10 years.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that Beijing has had 600,000 mobile phone
subscribers since 1987, when the first mobile phone was opened in
the city. There are 5.5 mobile phones among every 100 residents in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The mobile phone users in Beijing numbered only 77,000 in 1994
and increased to 288,000 at the end of 1996.
</P>
<P>
To meet the increasing demand of customers, Beijing Telecom's
digital mobile phone network has been increased four times and has
a handling capacity of 760,000 lines.
</P>
<P>
Now, the network has more than 360 standard stations for the
phones, which have been linked up with 30 of the country's 32
provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions, as well as with
13 countries and regions including Singapore, Finland, Germany,
Hong Kong and Macao.
</P>
<P>
With technology and equipment imported from US's Motorola and
Finland's Nokia, the fifth expansion of the city's digital mobile
network has started to increase its handling capacity to
1.15 million lines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
