<HEADLINE> Guangxi Forms Large Conglomerate for Reclamation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, December 29 (Xinhua) -- The recent setup of the
Guangxi Reclamation Group Co. Ltd indicates that agricultural
reclamation in the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region has climbed to a
new high.
</P>
<P>
The State-owned company has a total registered capital of
540 million yuan (65 million U.S. dollars). It manages 153,400
hectares of land and employs more than 70,000 people.
</P>
<P>
The company is expected to be a major center for fine crop
strains breeding, agricultural research and commodity export in
the region.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi's reclamation projects, which largely adopt machinery
in agricultural production, have been playing an important role in
the overall development of local agriculture, industry and trade.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the sector had a gross domestic product (GDP) of 624
million yuan (75 million U.S. dollars) and contributed 174 million
yuan (20 million U.S. dollars) to the region in tax revenue.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi's reclamation projects focus on crop growing, animal
husbandry and aquatic production. The sector has 15,000 hectares
planted with sugar cane, 8,628 hectares with fruit, 2,525 hectares
with tea, 3,269 hectares with sisal hemp, 4,777 hectares of rubber
trees and 21,500 hectares of cash forests.
</P>
<P>
Their major products are pigs, cows, prawns and freshwater
fish. In 1996, 213,800 hogs were slaughtered at reclamation farms
here.
</P>
<P>
The reclamation company will further strengthen the sector's
competitiveness. Its business will also involve inter-provincial
trade, border trade, wholesales of farm products, tourism, catering,
real estate development and transportation services. 
</P>
