<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, December 29 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Governor Frank Keating of Oklahoma of the United
States said Sunday he wanted Terry Nicols sentenced to death for
his role in the 1995 Oklahoma bombing, regardless of a jury's
mixed verdict earlier this week.
</P>
<P>
The federal jury in Denver, Colorado, found Nicols guilty of
conspiracy and involuntary manslaughter, but not murder. The
penalty phase of the trial is scheduled to begin Monday.
</P>
<P>
The blast of a federal building on April 19, 1995, killed 168
people and injured hundreds more. (US-Oklahoma)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- A 50-year-old Moroccan man was killed in a fire which
devastated a running down apartment building in central Paris
Sunday, said police.
</P>
<P>
The fire could be caused by an accident in the big building
which was illegally occupied by some 365 North African and black
African people, as the government banned people from inhabiting
the house in July 1997.
</P>
<P>
The mayoral office of Paris said that it had put into place
immediately all the necessary measures to rehouse the people
living in the building, which is situated on Rue Louvel-Tessier in
the 10th district of Paris. (France-Paris-Fire)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Pro-British guerrillas said Sunday they killed a
former Irish republican prisoner in a gun attack in Northern
Ireland.
</P>
<P>
The man killed was Seamus Dillon, who had served 14 years in
jail for a 1980 murder linked to the province's political and
religious conflict.
</P>
<P>
The attack by the Loyalist Volunteer Force Saturday night was
in reprisal for the killing hours earlier of their leader, Billy
Wright, by Irish republican prisoners inside a top-security jail,
according to reports from Belfast, capital of the
province. (UK-N.Ireland-Killing)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraq said Sunday the recent U.S. talks with Turkey
on protecting Kurds in northern Iraq revealed the two are
conspiring to carry out a U.S.-British scheme of interfering in
Iraq's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
The official Iraqi News Agency quoted an unidentified spokesman
as saying the U.S. has been, and is still working to spread
disorder and instability in northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman accused Washington of making northern Iraq an
arena for bloody internal conflicts and a target of Turkish
military attacks and invasion as well as foreign intelligence
violations. (Iraq-US-Spokesman)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NAIROBI -- Kenyan presidential candidate Setphen Omondi Oludhe,
the leader of the tiny Economic Independence Party, announced
Sunday the final campaign day that he quit the race to support
President Daniel arap Moi's bid.
</P>
<P>
Moi, 73 and in power for 19 years, is "a wise and able" leader
to be voted for on Monday, the polling day, he was quoted by
local sources as saying in Kisumu, the third-largest city of
Kenya.
</P>
<P>
Oludhe's party, set up late last month, was the youngest party
in the campaign with Moi's 37-year-old ruling Kenya African
National Union the oldest. (Kenya-Presidential Election)
</P>
