<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ancient Ruins Discovered in Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, December 29 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Archeologists recently
discovered three ancient ruins along the Hanjiang River in central
China.
</P>
<P>
The ruins belong to the Old Stone Age and the distance between
them is only dozens of kilometers. One of the three is near Yunxian
County, where an ancient human head fossil was found in May, 1989.
</P>
<P>
More than 300 stone-made tools were found in the
ruins, including picks, axes and choppers.
</P>
<P>
Experts said the new discovery will benefit the study of
culture in central China, which is inhabited by the people from
north and south China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
